div.p:
1. That his whole Life (according to the Account that is given of it by the Evangeliſts, which we now build upon, as true) was in all Reſpects ſpotleſs and unblameable;
                     1 Pet. 2.22. 1 Pet. 1.19. 
                     He did no Sin, neither was Guile found in his Mouth; He was a Lamb without blemiſh and without ſpot. And this he himſelf urges as a Reaſon why his Teſtimony ought to be credited; Joh. viii. 46. Which of you convinceth me of Sin? and if I ſay the Truth why do ye not believe me? And a very good Reaſon it was; for it could not juſtly be ſuſpected, that a Perſon of whom no other ill thing could be ſaid, was yet indeed in the whole Courſe of his Life guilty of a Crime of the greateſt Magnitude, viz. of Lying in the Name of God; of ſaying, that the Lord had ſent him, when indeed the Lord had not ſent him, nor ſpoken by him.
